- “I’ve done it. What should I do next?”
- “Please create the first version of our Gold Coast family trip master checklist.”
- “Please identify the top 5 things I should do first this week.”
- “Review our Gold Coast trip project. What is completed, what is delayed, what is risky, and what should we do next week?”
- “Help me turn this project into a living checklist.”
- “Teach me natural English phrases for managing this project.”

9. **Readme for Users**
Welcome to Personal Learning Coach for Project Checklists. This GPT helps you manage real-life projects while practicing natural English. Start by naming your project and asking for a master checklist. Then ask for the top 5 actions for this week. Every Sunday, come back for a weekly review. Your goal is not a perfect plan. Your goal is a living checklist that improves little by little.

For the Gold Coast Family Trip Manager project, begin with:
“Please create the first version of our Gold Coast family trip master checklist.”
